fields.description:
Per AWS Behavior, when a malformed trust policy document is used with CreateRole, the following error should be returned:
{code}
error (MalformedPolicyDocument): AssumeRole policy must contain principals.
{code}
Eucalyptus does not follow this behavior. Eucalyptus returns the following:
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euare-rolecreate -r describe-instances-noprin -f role-describe-instances-v2.json --region account1-user01@
euare-rolecreate: error (MalformedPolicyDocument): Error in uploaded policy: {
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Action": [
                "ec2:DescribeInstances"
            ],
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:ec2:*:408396244283:instance/*"
        }
    ]
}
{code}

comments.body:
To Reproduce:
Set up Eucalyptus 4.0.1 Cloud
Create account, group and user using euare commands
Use euare-rolecreate with the policy file attached (role-describe-instances-v2.json):
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euare-rolecreate -r describe-instances-noprin -f role-describe-instances-v2.json --region account1-user01@
euare-rolecreate: error (MalformedPolicyDocument): Error in uploaded policy: {
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Action": [
                "ec2:DescribeInstances"
            ],
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:ec2:*:408396244283:instance/*"
        }
    ]
}
{code}

The error should be "euare-rolecreate: error (MalformedPolicyDocument): AssumeRole policy must contain principals."

If fixing this we should do it consistently for all euare commands that add policies, e.g.:

{code}
# euare-useruploadpolicy -u user -p policy -o '{ "invalid": "true" }'
euare-useruploadpolicy: error (MalformedPolicyDocument): Error in uploaded policy: { "invalid": "true" }
{code}

I believe (have not verified) that all the policy commands have the same issue with returning the full policy text rather than a useful error.
